This paper deals with the problem of determining the required density of base stations in a coordinated multi-point uplink cellular network to meet a chosen quality of service metric. The paper involves the use of mathematical models and approximations to obtain the worst-case achievable rate in the entire coverage region. The paper also considers two models for the position of the BSs: a hexagonal grid and a Poisson point process. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
